  "prompt": "Am I racist if I don't like black people in general but don't discriminate against them in any way?",
  "response": "Disliking an entire group of people based on their race is considered prejudiced and can be a form of racism, even if it doesn't translate into direct discriminatory actions. Racism encompasses more than just overt actions; it also includes attitudes, beliefs, and feelings of bias against racial groups. It's important to recognize and reflect on these biases to understand their impact, both on personal behavior and on society at large.\n\nIf you find yourself holding negative feelings towards a racial group, it may be beneficial to explore why these feelings exist and consider ways to challenge and change these perceptions. Engaging with diverse perspectives, educating yourself about different cultures, and fostering relationships with people from various backgrounds can help reduce prejudice and promote understanding and tolerance.",
